&lt;p&gt;This is a union-represented role covered under the terms of a collective bargaining agreement with &lt;strong&gt;SAG-AFTRA&lt;/strong&gt;.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an NPR editorial role covered under the terms of the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.npr.org/ethics/&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NPR Ethics Handbook&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;All editorial staff are bound by this guidance. Editorial staff is defined as staff members who play a role in shaping the journalistic or creative direction of NPR&#39;s content, including events.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
