&lt;p&gt;As our IT Network Manager, you will bridge the gap between traditional enterprise networking and the cutting edge of broadcast technology. We are looking for a Cisco-certified leader to oversee the lifecycle of our network infrastructure, specifically optimizing for real-time media transport. Beyond technical mastery, you will act as a collaborative partner to our IT and production teams, fostering a culture of high availability and proactive security. If you thrive in &#39;always-on&#39; environments and have a passion for seamless media delivery, this is your next challenge&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and support enterprise network infrastructure including Cisco ACI, Catalyst and Nexus switches, Firepower (FTD), SD-WAN, Routers and Meraki platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage and lead a team of network and voice engineers, effective network and telecom project management, performance management, and professional development.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide expertise in Storage Area Networking (SAN), including Fibre Channel (FC) and FCoE, with hands-on experience in VSAN design, zoning, and integration with Cisco Nexus and MDS platforms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with broadcast engineering teams on implementing and maintaining a high-availability IP broadcast network that carries low-latency, real-time audio and video traffic for NPR’s daily content production and live transmission.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee design, implementation, and optimization of LAN/WAN and wireless networks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Configure and maintain routing protocols (BGP, EIGRP).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead network operations, troubleshooting, and root-cause analysis for complex issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Utilize monitoring and analytics tools such as SolarWinds and Cisco Nexus Dashboard&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use advanced network visibility tools to analyze performance across internet paths.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure network reliability, performance, scalability, and security across the organization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain network architecture documentation, diagrams, and operational procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Security, DevOps, Systems, and Enterprise application teams to support enterprise services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate effectively with senior leadership, providing clear documentation, analysis, and insights on network performance, risks, incidents and strategic initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
